.NET SENIOR DEVELOPER
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 07:40:38
Ref. JB3045678
Job Description
The .NET Senior Developer will be part of a large team of application developers where he/she will design, develop, implement and support applications and integration solutions across the business. In addition to business users in other departments, the .NET Senior Developer will be expected to interact with other software developers having diverse vertical expertise and skills.
Key Responsibilities:
• Interacting with internal business users and identifying tasks which require automation and defining projects
• Analyse business requirements, translate to technical requirements, and define functional & design specifications
• Mapping requirements and recommend appropriate technology for the business requirement, as per budgets
• Defining architectural design, database design, and user-interface design, coding standard, setup & deployment
• Estimating effort and cost, and scheduling the activities together with Project Manager
• Defining project plans & schedules, resource allocations as per budgets together with Project Manager
• Requirement elicitation and process mapping
• Application/Framework Design
• Development of robust and user-friendly .NET based web applications
• T-SQL Development
• Routine daily maintenance of existing applications
Skills
Key Skills/Expertise:
• 5+ years of experience in rapid application development on .NET framework
• Solid understanding of Object Oriented Design and Programming.
• Strong experience in database design and optimisation.
• Expert user of Team Foundation Server
• Strong experience with design patterns
• Solid understanding of the importance of User eXperience Design (UXD)
• Strong knowledge of software implementation best practices.
• Good experience in working with n-tier architectures along with a clear understanding of the service-oriented architectures (SOA) concept.
• Candidate must be an expert on Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC),
• Experience of agile and scrum methodologies is a definite plus
• Experience of Test Driven Development (TDD) is a definite plus
• Experience in Mobile App development for iOS, Android and BlackBerry is a definite plus
Communication Skills:
• Excellent written and spoken English skills. Must be able to communicate clearly.
• Able to communicate technical information to both technical and non-technical audiences.
• Self-motivated, responsible team-player who is passionate about building high-quality systems using software implementation best practices.
• Excellent analytical, programming, troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.
Technologies:
• .NET Framework
• C#
• Forms/MVC
• HTML5 and CSS
• JQuery/AJAX/ JavaScript
• Entity Framework
• WCF/Web Services
• LINQ
• T-SQL
• WPF/Silverlight
• Objective-C
This job is posted in the following Specialties:
